# Coverage exclusions — regex patterns matched against lines of the
# raw `go test -coverprofile` output, applied before the 100% gate
# by covgate (https://github.com/kfet/covgate).
#
# Convention: file-level patterns only. No line numbers, no
# per-function regexes — both rot on any nearby edit. Whole files,
# whole subpackages, whole generated bundles are fine.

# Entry-point shims: cmd/<binary>/main.go (kept for future binaries —
# pinoauth currently ships none).
^github.com/kfet/pinoauth/cmd/[^/]+/main\.go:

# Per-feature `<feature>_must.go` files. Each holds the `mustX` helpers
# for the feature in `<feature>.go`: tiny wrappers that panic on
# structurally-unreachable error paths (kernel CSPRNG failure, Serve
# on a private listener, http.NewRequestWithContext on a validated
# URL, …). Keeping them in a sibling file means the helper sits next
# to the code that uses it, the name signals intent (`mustReadRandom`,
# `mustServeLoopback`), and the file-level coverage exclusion stays
# narrow and meaningful.
_must\.go:
